---
const localPrompt = `You are running in a local AI coding tool or terminal-based agent.

Your job: create a simple memory folder that future AI sessions can read and update.

Before you start, confirm you can:
- create and edit files in this folder
- run shell commands, if this tool supports them
- use git only if this folder already uses git

If you cannot create files here, stop and tell me to use the web/manual prompt instead.

Use the current folder name as the project name.

Create this structure:
- memory/state.json
- memory/global/lessons/
- memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/
- memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/

Create or update the startup rules file for this tool:
- AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, or the closest equivalent

The startup rules must say:
- At the start of a session, identify the current project.
- Before meaningful work, read memory/global/lessons/ and this project's lessons.
- If memory/projects/[project-name]/ does not exist, create it.
- At the end of a meaningful session, write a session note.
- If the same lesson appears across projects, move it to memory/global/lessons/.
- Keep startup context short. Keep raw session notes searchable.
- The human sets goals. The AI keeps the memory files up to date.

Create three reusable prompt snippets:

/init-project
- Detect the project name.
- Create memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/.
- Create memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/.
- Add a short README for the project memory folder.

/end-session
- Summarize what changed.
- Capture decisions, commands that worked, commands that failed, and lessons.
- Save the note to memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-short-goal.md.
- If a lesson is reusable, also save it to memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/.
- Update memory/state.json.

/distill
- Review recent session notes.
- Merge repeated project lessons.
- Move cross-project lessons to memory/global/lessons/.
- Update memory/state.json.

Use these note shapes:
- Session note: frontmatter with type, project, date, goal, outcome. Sections: Goal, What Changed, Decisions, Commands, Lessons, Follow-Up.
- Project lesson: frontmatter with type, scope, project, created_at, source_sessions. Sections: Rule, Why, How to Apply, Boundaries.
- Global lesson: frontmatter with type, scope, created_at, promoted_from, projects_seen. Sections: Rule, Why This Became Global, How Future Sessions Should Use It, Exceptions.

Initialize memory/state.json with:
- created_at
- last_distill_at
- projects
- global_lesson_count
- session_count

Then run /init-project for this folder.

Finish by telling me:
- which files you created or changed
- which project name you used
- how the next AI session should load memory
- what to run at the end of a session`;

const webPrompt = `You are in web/manual mode.

You cannot save files for me. Do not say files were saved unless I confirm I saved them.

Your job: output the exact files I should save so future AI chats can reuse memory.

Ask me for the project name if you do not know it.

Generate these files:
- MEMORY_START_HERE.md
- memory/state.json
- memory/projects/[project-name]/README.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-first-setup.md
- memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/how-to-use-memory.md

For each file, use this format:

FILE: path/to/file.md
Then put the full file content in one fenced code block.

MEMORY_START_HERE.md must tell future chats:
- Read this file first.
- Ask me to paste or attach memory/state.json.
- Ask me to paste or attach relevant files from memory/global/lessons/.
- Ask me to paste or attach relevant files from memory/projects/[project-name]/lessons/.
- Before meaningful work, summarize what memory says.
- At the end of meaningful work, output a new session note for me to save.
- If a reusable lesson appears, output a project lesson for me to save.
- If a lesson applies across projects, tell me it belongs in memory/global/lessons/.
- Do not claim anything was saved until I confirm it.

memory/state.json must include:
- created_at
- last_distill_at
- projects
- global_lesson_count
- session_count

The first session note must include:
- frontmatter with type, project, date, goal, outcome
- Goal
- What Changed
- Decisions
- Commands
- Lessons
- Follow-Up

The first project lesson must include:
- frontmatter with type, scope, project, created_at
- Rule
- Why
- How to Apply
- Boundaries

After the file blocks, give me a short checklist:
- which files to save
- where to paste MEMORY_START_HERE.md if my web tool has project instructions
- what files to paste or attach at the start of the next chat
- what to ask for at the end of the next chat`;
---

<div class="prompt-tabs" data-prompt-tabs>
	<div class="prompt-tabs-header">
		<div>
			<p class="prompt-tabs-kicker">Choose one prompt</p>
			<p class="prompt-tabs-copy">Pick the setup that matches how you use AI.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="prompt-tab-list" role="tablist" aria-label="Setup prompt type">
			<button
				type="button"
				class="prompt-tab is-active"
				id="local-prompt-tab"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="true"
				aria-controls="local-prompt-panel"
				data-prompt-tab="local"
			>
				Local tool
			</button>
			<button
				type="button"
				class="prompt-tab"
				id="web-prompt-tab"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="false"
				aria-controls="web-prompt-panel"
				data-prompt-tab="web"
			>
				Web/manual
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>

	<section
		class="prompt-panel is-active"
		id="local-prompt-panel"
		role="tabpanel"
		aria-labelledby="local-prompt-tab"
		data-prompt-panel="local"
	>
		<div class="prompt-panel-bar">
			<p>Use this when the AI tool can create files in your folder.</p>
			<button type="button" class="copy-prompt-button" data-copy-prompt>Copy local prompt</button>
		</div>
		<pre tabindex="0"><code>{localPrompt}</code></pre>
	</section>

	<section
		class="prompt-panel"
		id="web-prompt-panel"
		role="tabpanel"
		aria-labelledby="web-prompt-tab"
		data-prompt-panel="web"
		hidden
	>
		<div class="prompt-panel-bar">
			<p>Use this when the AI is in a web chat and you will save the files yourself.</p>
			<button type="button" class="copy-prompt-button" data-copy-prompt>Copy web prompt</button>
		</div>
		<pre tabindex="0"><code>{webPrompt}</code></pre>
	</section>
</div>

<script is:inline>
	(() => {
		const copyText = async (text, button, codeBlock) => {
			const originalLabel = button.textContent;

			try {
				await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
				button.textContent = "Copied";
			} catch {
				const range = document.createRange();
				range.selectNodeContents(codeBlock);
				const selection = window.getSelection();
				selection.removeAllRanges();
				selection.addRange(range);
				button.textContent = "Selected";
			}

			window.setTimeout(() => {
				button.textContent = originalLabel;
			}, 1800);
		};

		document.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-tabs]").forEach((root) => {
			const tabs = Array.from(root.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-tab]"));
			const panels = Array.from(root.querySelectorAll("[data-prompt-panel]"));

			tabs.forEach((tab) => {
				tab.addEventListener("click", () => {
					const target = tab.getAttribute("data-prompt-tab");

					tabs.forEach((item) => {
						const isActive = item === tab;
						item.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
						item.setAttribute("aria-selected", String(isActive));
					});

					panels.forEach((panel) => {
						const isActive = panel.getAttribute("data-prompt-panel") === target;
						panel.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
						panel.hidden = !isActive;
					});
				});
			});

			root.querySelectorAll("[data-copy-prompt]").forEach((button) => {
				button.addEventListener("click", () => {
					const panel = button.closest("[data-prompt-panel]");
					const codeBlock = panel.querySelector("code");
					copyText(codeBlock.textContent, button, codeBlock);
				});
			});
		});
	})();
</script>

<style>
	.prompt-tabs {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 1rem auto 0;
		border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fff;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-header {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		background: #f9fafb;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-kicker,
	.prompt-tabs-copy,
	.prompt-panel-bar p {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.prompt-tabs-kicker {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--black);
	}

	.prompt-tabs-copy {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
	}

	.prompt-tab-list {
		display: inline-flex;
		gap: 0.25rem;
		padding: 0.25rem;
		border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fff;
	}

	.prompt-tab,
	.copy-prompt-button {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		border-radius: 6px;
		cursor: pointer;
	}

	.prompt-tab {
		padding: 0.45rem 0.7rem;
		background: transparent;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.prompt-tab.is-active {
		background: var(--accent);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.prompt-panel-bar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.prompt-panel-bar p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--gray-dark);
	}

	.copy-prompt-button {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
		background: var(--black);
		color: #fff;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.copy-prompt-button:hover {
		background: var(--accent);
	}

	.prompt-panel pre {
		margin: 0;
		border-radius: 0;
		max-height: 32rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.prompt-tabs-header,
		.prompt-panel-bar {
			align-items: stretch;
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		.prompt-tab-list,
		.copy-prompt-button {
			width: 100%;
		}

		.prompt-tab {
			flex: 1 1 0;
		}
	}
</style>
